🔥 7. Security Model of PHS
✔ No real password is synced
Only:

NT hash → re‑hashed → irreversible

✔ Hash cannot be reversed
SHA‑256 transformation is one-way.
✔ Sync uses secure channels
Encrypted communication between AAD Connect and cloud.
✔ Works with Identity Protection
Risk signals (e.g., leaked credentials, impossible travel) can be applied only when cloud controls authentication.

🧯 8. When PHS Should NOT Be Used
Rare scenarios:
❌ Strict compliance requires password NEVER leaving AD
(even hashed)
→ Choose PTA or federation.
❌ Apps rely on on-prem password validation
Very rare; usually legacy.
❌ You want full control of authentication logs on-prem
Only some regulated industries.

